         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Richmond ¶ April 1 /78 ¶ My dear Doctor, ¶  ¶ Our venerable friend Mr Clarke is better, but I do not think he will be able to take part again in public affairs ¶  ¶ With regard to  ¶ Sparganium ¶ , yo...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.04.01</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From William Woolls</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M46, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Verbesina encelioides </seg>var<seg style="font-style: italic; "> encelioides</seg> (MEL 2169904), collected by Woolls as <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Wedelia">Wedelia</name>
                     </seg>, 1878.</p>
               </note>Richmond<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">NSW.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">April 1 /78</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Doctor,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Our venerable friend Mr Clarke is better, but I do not think he will be able to take part again in public affairs<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">W. B. Clarke died on 16 June 1878.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With regard to <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Sparganium</hi>
               </seg>, you may recollect that I forwarded to you Brown's S. <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">angustifolium</hi>
               </seg> from Parramatta.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">R. Brown (1810), p. 338.</p>
               </note> The Richmond plant seems different, &amp; identical with the figure of <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">S. simplex</hi>
               </seg> in Baxter's British Phenogamous Botany Vol. 4. p. 276.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Baxter (1843).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I should like to see a tracing of <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">E. punctata</hi>
               </seg>. It has been considered as a variety of E. <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">tereticornis</hi>
               </seg>, but the operculum is always much shorter, the leaves differently veined, &amp; the wood tougher. I am inclined to think that the plant which I have hitherto regarded as <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">E. punctata</hi>
               </seg> is your E. <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Stuartiana</hi>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Wedelia">Wedelia</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> to which I refer is spreading widely in the low lands. It is not any of those I think, described in the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Flora</hi>
               </seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham (1863-78), vol. 3, pp. 537-9.</p>
               </note> The leaves are sessile, &amp; the achenes winged. The shape of the leaf is peculiar. Should it be necessary, I will send a better specimen.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours very sincerely</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>W. Woolls</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
